name: Sticker-art
description:
About model
Style model for Stable Diffusion. Its main purposes are stickers and t-shirt design.

Copyrights and support
If you like what I am doing and you want to support my current and upcoming projects: here is my coffee jar

I am a huge fan of open source - you can use it however you like with only restrictions for selling my models. If you like it - I will appreciate your support. I spend real money on training. Cheers!


Installation:
As it is a model based on 2.1 to make it work you need to use .yaml file with the name of a model (vector-art.yaml). The yaml file is included here as well to download. Simply copy paste to the same folder as selected model file. Usually, this is the models/Stable-diffusion one.

Versions:

Currently, there is only one version of this model - alpha.

Black images issue:

2.1 models need to have a web-ui config modified - if you are getting black images - go to your config file and add to COMMANDLINE_ARGS= --no-half - potentially it could work with --xformers instead (if supported). This line might slow your generation a bit but will not affect negatively your output.
